cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.LG 

The paper introduces a dynamic logic for trace properties that incorporates concepts from behavioral types and allows reasoning about non-functional properties within a sequent calculus. It also presents a sequent calculus for object-oriented actors with futures that integrates a pointer analysis and bridges the gap between behavioral types and deductive verification. These topics are closely related to programming languages (cs.PL), logic (cs.LO), software engineering (cs.SE), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and machine learning (cs.LG).
